#cli #spec #workflow
> Agent skill templates bundled with eshp for AI-assisted workflows.

Three skill templates ship with eshp in the skills/ directory:

  eshp--plan              Plan and design features using the eshp memory graph.
                          Guides an agent to query eshp for context before implementing.
  eshp--commit-and-dream  Commit WIP to git, then reflect on the session and
                          update the memory graph. Prunes stale info too.
  eshp--deep-dream        Deep maintenance pass on the memory graph. Checks graph
                          accuracy against the codebase, consolidates tags/rels,
                          adds missing entries, then commits updated memory files.

init-skills command
  eshp init-skills <path> [--force]
  Copies all bundled skills to <path>/<skill-name>/SKILL.md.
  Creates directories as needed. --force to overwrite existing files.
  Templates live in skills/ next to eshp_cli.py (Path(__file__).parent / "skills").
  Included in the wheel via pyproject.toml: include = ["skills/**"]

Typical invocation:
  eshp init-skills .github/skills          # GitHub Copilot agent
  eshp init-skills .cursor/skills          # Cursor
  eshp init-skills .rules/skills           # custom agents

Note: skills/ at the repo root is the canonical template source.
The .github/skills/ folder in this repo is an example instantiation of those templates.
When templates are updated, re-run init-skills to propagate changes.

